Basic description: Sticks a target to the ground, making them unable to move. This spell can partially overcome innate magic resistance.<br>
Raw data: <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spell.html?id=3194&source=Live">lucy.fnord.net/spell.html...ource=Live</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
Whizbang's notes: Our final root spell is only a modest upgrade to Fetter. The much-touted semi-lure effect on Greater Fetter doesn't seem to have as much of an impact as that same effect has with Draught of Ro, Draught of Thunder and Draught of E'ci. It also costs more mana. While I use Greater Fetter myself, I can certainly understand those who stick with Fetter.<br>
Spell era: Planes of Power<br>
Vendor information: This spell is not sold by any known NPC.<br>
Research information: This spell cannot be researched.<br>
Quest information: This spell is a random award for turning in an ethereal parchment to Channeler Olaemos in the Plane of Knowledge.<br>
Drop information: This spell is not dropped by any known NPC.<br>
<br>
Lure of Thunder<br>
Basic description: This spell releases a difficult to resist blast of lightning, striking a single target.<br>
Raw data: <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spell.html?id=3328&source=Live">lucy.fnord.net/spell.html...ource=Live</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
Whizbang's notes: Our sole vendor-sold post-60 spell is nice, if not necessarily terribly sexy. It's big, it hits well, but most scenarios where one would need a lure post-60 already have other raid team members debuffing. Still, there are those who use this spell in preference to Ice Spear of Solist if they do not have Sunstrike and can not yet scribe Draught of Ro.<br>
Spell era: Planes of Power<br>
Vendor information: The Plane of Knowledge, Myrist, Channeler Keatrem<br>
Research information: This spell cannot be researched.<br>
Quest information: This spell is not a quest reward in any known quests.<br>
Drop information: This spell is not dropped by any known NPC.<br>
<br>
Resistant Armor<br>
Basic description: Improves your resistance to disease and poison.<br>
Raw data: <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spell.html?id=3326&source=Live">lucy.fnord.net/spell.html...ource=Live</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
Whizbang's notes: This long overdue upgrade to Resistant Skin is nice, but not worth the extreme wait. Still, it has its uses.<br>
Spell era: Planes of Power<br>
Vendor information: This spell is not sold by any known NPC.<br>
Research information: This spell cannot be researched.<br>
Quest information: This spell is a random award for turning in an ethereal parchment to Channeler Olaemos in the Plane of Knowledge.<br>
Drop information: This spell is not dropped by any known NPC.<br>
<br>
Shield of the Arcane<br>
Basic description: This spell creates an invisible field of energy around you, raising hit points, armor class and magic resistance.<br>
Raw data: <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spell.html?id=3300&source=Live">lucy.fnord.net/spell.html...ource=Live</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
Whizbang's notes: Our next to last shielding spell is extremely potent and a large jump in power.<br>
Spell era: Planes of Power<br>
Vendor information: This spell is not sold by any known NPC.<br>
Research information: This spell cannot be researched.<br>
Quest information: This spell is a random award for turning in an ethereal parchment to Channeler Olaemos in the Plane of Knowledge.<br>
Drop information: This spell is not dropped by any known NPC.<br>
<br>
Tears of Ro<br>
Basic description: An area of effect rain spell that does its damage on up to three targets in multiple waves of damage.<br>
Raw data: <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spell.html?id=3327&source=Live">lucy.fnord.net/spell.html...ource=Live</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
Whizbang's notes: A devastatingly powerful rain spell, either used singly or when twisted together with previous tears spells.<br>
Spell era: Planes of Power<br>
Vendor information: This spell is not sold by any known NPC.<br>
Research information: This spell cannot be researched.<br>
Quest information: This spell is a random award for turning in an ethereal parchment to Channeler Olaemos in the Plane of Knowledge.<br>
